{
  "texts": [
    "Ablation studies confirm the importance of the planner and extractor: the former decomposes complex queries, while the latter improves retrieval precision.",
    "Strategic allocation of model capacity across agents yields further gains in both performance and efficiency.",
    "Together, these findings highlight the potential of modular, agent-based reasoning as a scalable and adaptable approach to improving retrieval-augmented generation.",
    "A.1 DETAILS OF EXPERIMENTAL DATASET",
    "We evaluate our method on five publicly available QA benchmarks that cover both single-hop and multi-hop reasoning."
  ]
}